Array Limitations : 
        int a[]= new int[5]
        
 1> Size Fix
 2> Typesafe 
 
 
 
 Collection framework:-  " java.util.* "
 
                          
                          Iterable(I)---------------------------------------------------------------
                             |                                                                      |                                            
                          Collections(I)                                                            |
                             |                                                                      |  
                             |Data value                                                            |
                             |                                                                      |
      -------------------------------------------------------------                                Map (Key,Value)
      |                             |                             |                                 |
     List(I)                     Set(I)                       Queue(I)                              | HashMap(C)
      |                             |                             |									| LinkedHashMap(C)
      |	ArrayList(C)                | HashSet(C)                  |-PriorityQueue(C)				| TreeMap (C)
      | Vector(C)                   | LinkedHashSet(C)
      | LinkedList(C)               | TreeSet(C)
    
    C- Classes
    I -Interfaces
    
    1> Difference between List vs Map or Set vs Map or queue vs Map
      
       List/set/queue inherit collection interface , whereas Map inherit iterable interface
       List/set/queue can accept data values, whereas Map accpets (key,value) pair
       
       
       
 primitive data types <=======>     wrapper classes
 1> byte                             Byte
 2> char                             Character
 3> int                              Integer
 4> long                             Long
 5> float                            Float
 6> double                           Double
 7> booleam                          Boolean
 8> short                            Short
 
 1 lakh record, arraylist will become slow 
 
 want to insert a record at 50,000 th position, nodes from 50,000 to 1,00,000 will shift 
 
 
 LinkedList : Double LinkedList  
 
 Single node : 1> will store the address of previous node, 2> will store the address of its own
 no shifting required for inserting or deleting a node
 
 Vector List :  methods synchronised
 ArrayList : unsynchronised
 
 
 Banking application : Synchronised
 
 100 request : 100 threads 
 for accepting the 2nd request, user has to finish the process for the 1st request
 
 Unsynchronised
 
 100 request  : 100 threads
 user can complete and accept simultaneous request